        <heading>2948.  Termination of conventional sequestration by the depositary</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2948.  Termination of conventional sequestration by the depositary
The depositary may terminate the conventional sequestration unilaterally only if he is unable to perform his obligations.  He is bound to deliver the thing to the successor depositary agreed upon by the parties and, when the parties cannot agree, he must apply to the court for the appointment of another depositary.</p>
        </content>
